166
00:07:45,530 --> 00:07:48,910
PCA is frequently used for
visualization where you reduce

167
00:07:48,910 --> 00:07:53,065
data to two or three
numbers so you can plot it.

168
00:07:53,065 --> 00:07:55,690
Like you saw in an earlier
video with the data

169
00:07:55,690 --> 00:07:56,860
on different countries so you

170
00:07:56,860 --> 00:07:58,885
can visualize
different countries.

171
00:07:58,885 --> 00:08:01,150
There are some other
applications of

172
00:08:01,150 --> 00:08:03,850
PCA that you may
occasionally hear about.

173
00:08:03,850 --> 00:08:06,365
That used to be more popular,

174
00:08:06,365 --> 00:08:10,295
maybe 10,15, 20 years ago
but much less so now.

175
00:08:10,295 --> 00:08:13,630
Another possible use of
PCA is data compression.

176
00:08:13,630 --> 00:08:15,580
For example, if you have

177
00:08:15,580 --> 00:08:18,385
a database of lots
of different cars,

178
00:08:18,385 --> 00:08:21,505
and you have 50
features per car,

179
00:08:21,505 --> 00:08:24,040
but it's just taking
up too much space on

180
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,240
your database or maybe

181
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:28,040
transmitting 50 numbers
over the Internet,

182
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:30,040
just takes too long.

183
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:32,980
Then one thing you
could do is reduce

184
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:36,730
these 50 features to a
smaller number of features.

185
00:08:36,730 --> 00:08:39,340
It could be 10 features with

186
00:08:39,340 --> 00:08:42,485
10 axes or 10
principal components.

187
00:08:42,485 --> 00:08:45,730
You can visualize 10-dimensional
data that easily,

188
00:08:45,730 --> 00:08:48,730
but this is 1/5 of
the storage space,

189
00:08:48,730 --> 00:08:52,820
or maybe 1/5 over the network
transmission costs needed.

190
00:08:52,820 --> 00:08:54,935
Many years ago I saw

191
00:08:54,935 --> 00:08:57,950
PCA use for this
application and more often,

192
00:08:57,950 --> 00:09:01,000
but today with modern storage

193
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,100
being able to store
pretty large datasets

194
00:09:03,100 --> 00:09:04,490
and modern networking,

195
00:09:04,490 --> 00:09:08,755
able to transmit faster and
more data than ever before.

196
00:09:08,755 --> 00:09:12,845
I see this use much less often
as an application of PCA.

197
00:09:12,845 --> 00:09:15,040
One of the applications
of PCA that again

198
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:17,500
used to be more common
maybe 10 years ago,

199
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:20,000
20 years ago, but
much less so now is

200
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,275
using it to speed up

201
00:09:21,275 --> 00:09:23,485
training of a supervised
learning model.

202
00:09:23,485 --> 00:09:25,040
Where the idea is,

203
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:27,370
if you had 1,000 features,

204
00:09:27,370 --> 00:09:29,740
and having a 1,000 features may

205
00:09:29,740 --> 00:09:32,065
the supervised learning
algorithm runs you slowly.

206
00:09:32,065 --> 00:09:37,285
Maybe you can reduce it
to 100 features using PCA

207
00:09:37,285 --> 00:09:39,785
and then your dataset is
basically smaller and

208
00:09:39,785 --> 00:09:42,715
your supervised learning
algorithm may run faster.

209
00:09:42,715 --> 00:09:45,910
This used to make a difference
in the running time

210
00:09:45,910 --> 00:09:49,119
of some of the older generations
of learning algorithms,

211
00:09:49,119 --> 00:09:52,355
such as if you have had a
support vector machines.

212
00:09:52,355 --> 00:09:54,280
This will speed up a
support vector machine.

213
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:57,085
But it turns out with modern
machine learning algorithms,

214
00:09:57,085 --> 00:09:59,275
algorithms like deep learning,

215
00:09:59,275 --> 00:10:02,255
this doesn't actually
hold that much,

216
00:10:02,255 --> 00:10:04,450
and is much more common to

217
00:10:04,450 --> 00:10:06,880
just take the
high-dimensional dataset,

218
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:09,625
and feed it into say
your neural network.

219
00:10:09,625 --> 00:10:11,620
Rather than run PCA because

220
00:10:11,620 --> 00:10:14,350
PCA has some computational
cost as well.

221
00:10:14,350 --> 00:10:17,170
You may hear about this in some

222
00:10:17,170 --> 00:10:19,600
of the other research papers,

223
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:22,275
but I don't really see
this done much anymore.

224
00:10:22,275 --> 00:10:24,010
But the most common
thing that I use

225
00:10:24,010 --> 00:10:26,250
PCA for today is
visualization and then I

226
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:28,250
find it very useful to reduce

227
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:30,945
the dimensional data
to visualize it.

